# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CODEOWNERS – automatic review requests for the Message Gateway monorepo.
#
# GitHub (and the GitHub CLI) consult this file to pick reviewers for
# every pull request. The rule with the most specific match wins; a
# later rule does not override an earlier one. We use placeholder team
# names that match the org structure described in CONTRIBUTING.md §9
# (`@msg-gateway/backend`, `@msg-gateway/frontend`,
# `@msg-gateway/platform`, `@msg-gateway/security`) so swapping them
# out for the real teams is a search-and-replace when the GitHub org
# is bootstrapped.
#
# File location: `.github/CODEOWNERS` is the first path GitHub
# checks; falling back to `/CODEOWNERS` or `/docs/CODEOWNERS`. We keep
# it under `.github/` so the whole GitHub-level config sits in one
# directory.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Global default -------------------------------------------------------
# Everything that does not match a more specific rule below is owned
# by the platform team. Putting a default in the file (rather than
# relying on GitHub's "no owner" fallback) guarantees a review
# request is filed for every PR, even small doc edits.
*                                               @msg-gateway/platform

# --- Backend (Python / FastAPI) -------------------------------------------
/backend/                                        @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/Dockerfile                              @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/requirements*.txt                       @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/pyproject.toml                          @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/alembic.ini                             @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/alembic/                                @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/tests/                                  @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/db.py                               @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/config.py                           @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/main.py                             @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/api/                                @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/routes/                             @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/services/                           @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/adapters/                           @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/models/                             @msg-gateway/backend
/backend/app/observability/                      @msg-gateway/backend

# --- Frontend (Angular / TypeScript) --------------------------------------
/frontend/                                       @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/Dockerfile                             @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/package.json                           @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/package-lock.json                      @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/angular.json                           @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/karma.conf.js                          @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/nginx.conf                             @frontend
/frontend/.eslintrc.json                         @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/tailwind.config.js                     @msg-gateway/frontend
/frontend/src/                                   @msg-gateway/frontend

# --- Shared infra ---------------------------------------------------------
# The local stack is the contract both apps depend on; both teams
# should sign off on any change to it.
/docker-compose.yml                              @msg-gateway/platform @msg-gateway/backend @msg-gateway/frontend
/.env.example                                    @msg-gateway/platform

# --- CI / CD --------------------------------------------------------------
# CI is the local + remote gate; the platform team owns it but the
# backend / frontend leads are pulled in for stack-specific jobs.
/.github/workflows/ci.yml                        @msg-gateway/platform @msg-gateway/backend @msg-gateway/frontend
/.github/dependabot.yml                          @msg-gateway/platform
/.github/CODEOWNERS                              @msg-gateway/platform

# --- Security-sensitive files --------------------------------------------
# Anything that touches the security policy, secret handling, or
# PII redaction is owned by the security team. They are the final
# reviewers on these paths even if the platform team merges the PR.
SECURITY.md                                      @msg-gateway/security
/backend/app/observability/redact.py             @msg-gateway/security
